x^2 + 4Cx - 2Cy = (x+2C)^2-4C^2 - 2Cy = 0 
 (x+2C)^2 = 4C^2 + 2Cy = 2C(2C+y). 
 x_1 = -2C + \sqrt{2C(2C+y)} =\frac{-4C + \sqrt{16C^2 +8Cy}}{2}
